comments.body:
> My concern about non blocking is that this test will be ignored as noise.

Yes I agree, some kind of reliable notifications would be a must.

@wrabcak how about my webhook idea, running testing downstream in udica (triggered by merges into libpod master)?  That would make notification slightly easier as well.

@cevich @wrabcak Couldn't we just have a simple tests for shipping versions of udica to block changes to podman that make it fail, inside of the podman CI.

That we know if we are modifying the `podman inspect` code in such a way that would break shipping udica.
At which point we would need to get patches into udica to support the new format, or fix the inspect code.

> @wrabcak ...If you can help me to enable your CI in udica repo (ideally send some initial CI testing via PR), I would be happy about it.

Yes, this is my intention.  I think only notifying isn't good enough, we need both it and CI testing happening in Udica PRs vs podman master.

@wrabcak question:  Am I correct in believing Udica itself and it's testing is ***not*** sensitive to the podman version being used?  i.e. Udica does not adjust behavior for different versions of podman.  Correct?
